[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Annex 2[bold]Evidence from Citizens Advice[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The CA Consumer Service (advice line) received over a million contacts in 2012/13, relating to 837k individual cases. Of these issues, 173,562 (21% of all issues) were categorised with a complaint description of ‘substandard services’. These are summarised by Tier 1 issue (business area) in the table below:
[normal]Service[bold]Cases[bold]Broadcasting
[normal]127
[normal]Commercial Goods and Services
[normal]1110
[normal]House Fittings and Appliances
[normal]55219
[normal]Leisure
[normal]19069
[normal]Other Household Requirements
[normal]21242
[normal]Personal Goods and Services
[normal]18136
[normal]Professional and Financial Services
[normal]28126
[normal]Transport
[normal]30533
