[normal]Annex 4 [bold]Which? Evidence[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Complaints levels about services are quite high
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]A number of service providers do not take responsibility for problems
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]2 in five complaints aren’t resolved by the provider, although this varies by sector. And top reasons include a shifting of the blame.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Problems not being resolved by the provider seem most prevalent in:
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Trades services – 58%
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Airlines/holiday operators – 56%
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Car/vehicle repairs – 53%
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]That the problem was caused by circumstances out of their control – 26%
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]That another company was responsible – 15%
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]That it was not possible to fix the problem – 15%
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]That they have done what they had promised to do – 13%
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]That the terms and conditions of your contract said they weren’t liable – 11%
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]That the problem was caused by consumer – 10%
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The provider ignored the issue/gave no response – 9%
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]That they have complied with the industry standard – 9%
